Reasoning: The paper discusses the comparison of two different taggers for German language, one based on decision trees (a statistical approach) and the other based on rules (a rule-based approach). This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) which is a subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper deals with part-of-speech tagging which is a common task in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques (decision trees) and statistical analysis, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively. The paper also involves the use of an external lexicon (Gertwol system) which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
